<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6472> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6472" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 46, Pontifices. He died about 33 (Suet. Tib. 6.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6268> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6268" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Escaping from Perusia (see 41, Promagistrates), he attempted a rising in Campania, and was compelled to flee to Sicily, but when Sextus Pompey refused him the fasces he went to Greece and joined Mark Antony (Vell. 2.75.1 and 3, and 76. 1; and 77.3; Suet. TA. 4, and 6; Tac. Ann. 5.1; Dio 48.15.3-4, and 44.1; 54.7.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6230> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6230" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Retaining the insignia of the praetorship beyond the regular period, he attached himself to L. Antonius and followed him to Perusia (Suet. Tib. 4; cf. Vell. 2.75.1; and see 40, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6147> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6147" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Vell. 2.75. 1, a praetorius in 40; Suet. Tib. 4, where it is implied that his year of office preceded that of the outbreak of the Perusine war." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5862> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5862" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected in Scipio's place (Suet. Tib. 4.1; cf. Vell. 2.75.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5830> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5830" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate or Prefect (his title is not preserved), he settled veterans in colonies in Gaul, among them Arelate and Narbo (Suet. Tib. 4. 1). See CIL 12, pp. 83, and 521." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5744> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5744" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably Proquaestor in 47 (see 48, Quaestors), when in Caesar's service at Alexandria (Bell. Alex. 25; Suet. Tib. 4; Dio 42.40.6)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5640> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5640" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Suet. Tib. 4. Commanded in Caesar's fleet at Alexandria (Bell. Alex. 25.3; Suet. Tib. 4; Dio 42.40.6, late in 48 and early in 47)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10464> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10464" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/21> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Suet. Tib. 4.3. With Antony in Achaea from 40 until the Peace of Misenum of 39, at which point Claudius was permitted to return to Rome in safety. Possibly employed as an officer during this time with Antony, especially considering his frustration with Sex. Pompey for not having given him an appointment." .
